
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ginstall-info` baraye sabte dastoorat dar `info` system estefade mishavad. In dastoor baraye ezafe kardane etela'at dastoor be systeme `info` va dastrasi asan be rahnama baraye karbaran be kar miravad. Asasan, `ginstall-info` file-haye `info` ra be directory-haye monaseb copy mikonad va anha ra update mikonad ta be dorosti kar konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--dir-file=FILENAME` --> 📁 Specify filename baraye directory file (usually 'dir').  Agar zekr nashavad az directory default estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `--section=SECTION` --> 🧩 Specify section baraye directory file. In section moshakhas mikonad ke etela'at dar koja dar directory `info` zakhire shavad.
    🔹 `--quiet` --> 🤫 Sedaye kharoji ra kam mikonad. Faghat peygham-haye khatti ra namayesh midahad.
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Namayesh rahnama baraye dastoor.
    🔹 `--version` --> 版本 Namayesh version barname.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ginstall-info mycommand.info /usr/share/info

    🔹 File `mycommand.info` ra dar directory `/usr/share/info` sabt mikonad.

    $ ginstall-info --dir-file=/etc/info/dir mycommand.info

    🔹 File `mycommand.info` ra ba estefade az file directory `/etc/info/dir` sabt mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ginstall-info --section="My Programs" mycommand.info

    🔹 File `mycommand.info` ra dar section "My Programs" dar directory `info` sabt mikonad, ke karbar mitavanad ba dastoor `info "My Programs"` be an dastresi dashte bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ginstall-info` command is used to register commands in the `info` system. This command is used to add command information to the `info` system, allowing users to easily access the manual. Basically, `ginstall-info` copies the `info` files to the appropriate directories and updates them to work correctly.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--dir-file=FILENAME` --> 📁 Specify the filename for the directory file (usually 'dir'). If not specified, the default directory is used.
    🔹 `--section=SECTION` --> 🧩 Specify the section for the directory file. This section determines where the information will be stored in the `info` directory.
    🔹 `--quiet` --> 🤫 Reduces output noise. Only displays error messages.
    🔹 `--help` --> ℹ️ Display help for the command.
    🔹 `--version` --> 🔢 Display program version.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ginstall-info mycommand.info /usr/share/info

    🔹 Registers the file `mycommand.info` in the `/usr/share/info` directory.

    $ ginstall-info --dir-file=/etc/info/dir mycommand.info

    🔹 Registers the file `mycommand.info` using the directory file `/etc/info/dir`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ginstall-info --section="My Programs" mycommand.info

    🔹 Registers the file `mycommand.info` in the "My Programs" section in the `info` directory, which the user can access using the command `info "My Programs"`.
